main event: Royal Air Force jet fighters chased a mystery object reported traveling at 700 miles per hour over the English Channel in 1952.
interesting points: The object was detected on radar and the RAF scrambled Javelin fighters to chase it.
The object was reportedly capable of flying at over 1,100 miles per hour.
The Air Ministry confirmed the chase but said they could not explain what the object was, emphasizing that it was not a 'flying saucer'.
A later report suggested the sighting was likely due to a mirage or optical illusion caused by atmospheric conditions.
There were other reported sightings of unidentified flying objects over England around this time, including a 'flying golf ball' and an orange UFO observed for 30 seconds.
sighted object: A high-speed object detected on radar
